Central Springs CSD
August 9, 2018 at 1:50 PM ¬∑

Good Afternoon,
With school starting in under two weeks, it is important that all families planning on attending Central Springs Schools have their children registered. We use the registration data to determine elementary class sizes and middle school and high school use it to determine class sections.
Families can register online through Sunday, August 12th. After Sunday, families not registered will have to come into the school to fill out the paperwork and pay all their fees. Any elementary student not registered and fees paid will not be assigned to a teacher and will not be able sign up for a conference. Middle school and high school students must be registered with all fees paid in order to receive their school issued laptop/computer.
Thank you to all those who have already registered, hopefully we can get everyone registered by the end of the weekend.
We look forward to an awesome school year.

post_text: Hope everyone has had a great summer!!! Hard to believe it's getting to be that time of year again. Online registration is open as well. We are currently looking for anyone who would like to join our pto this upcoming school year, without our volunteers, we wouldn't be able to accomplish what we do through out the year for our school!! Watch our page for an update on the first meeting of the year and then we will decide on a day that works for monthly meetings throughout the year. Just a reminder we will have a collection for our box tops just like previous years. Bring them during before school conferences and drop them off. This time of year you can collect quite a few from the supplies you're purchasing already :) If interested in joining our PTO please send us a message or email: pto.manly@gmail.com with contact info and we can keep you up to date. Volunteer as much or as little, we know schedules get busy, and any little bit helps!!!
